    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource block allocation issue in nr_mac_rrc_data_ind_ue function\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_mac_rrc_data_ind_ue` function in `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/L2_interface_ue.c` was using an uninitialized variable `sdu_size` in error log messages instead of the actual `pdu_len` parameter. This caused incorrect error reporting when buffer overflow conditions occurred, potentially leading to improper handling of data in downstream functions and violating scheduling constraints.\n\nThis fix corrects the error log messages to use the proper `pdu_len` parameter value, ensuring accurate reporting of buffer overflow conditions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/L2_interface_ue.c`: Fixed error log messages in `nr_mac_rrc_data_ind_ue` function to use `pdu_len` instead of uninitialized `sdu_size` variable in two locations:\n  * Line 76: NR-BCCH-DL-SCH buffer overflow error message\n  * Line 104: NR_SBCCH_SL_BCH buffer overflow error message\n\n"
}